race.comment: TURN THE TIDE (8) boasts a consistent overall record including nine wins from 28 starts, the latest winning (34.43) over 600m at The Meadows. Goes very well here finding the frame in each of four starts. Drawn wide but with a clean break will be tough to beat again. HE SHINES (3) was sent out long odds last time but rocketed out of the boxes with a fast early sectional and gave a sight before being swallowed up late, finishing a 4.5 lengths second (29.60) over 515m at this track. Winning chance. PAW VORTEX (2) missed the frame last time, finishing 6th (29.88) last time in a Special conditions H at this track. Has won here at this journey. Has a solid record from this box including two wins and a minor placing. A big run wouldn't surprise. DESIRABILITY (1) generally performs well over this distance.
